<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 23 at 3:52PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...REDUCED VISIBILITY AND LOCALIZED ACCUMULATION IN BURSTS OF
HEAVIER LAKE EFFECT SNOW SHOWERS LATE THIS AFTERNOON...
Lake effect snow showers will continue to track across southern
portions of the county late this afternoon, generally along and
south of the I-69 corridor. The potential exists for the heaviest
bursts of snow to result in a rapid reduction in visibility below
1 mile and a quick accumulation of snow on roadways. Use caution
while driving and allow extra time to reach your destination. Be
prepared for variable road conditions and lowered visibilities.</description>
